            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="notes">Notes<a class="hash-link" href="#notes" title="Direct link to heading">â€‹</a></h2><p>Reading <a href="https://www.oreilly.co.jp/books/9784873119823/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Fundamentals of Software Architecture</a> by Mark Richards, Neal Ford, 2020, O'REILLY.</p><p>I'm writing down some keywords below...</p><ul><li><strong>Architecture Decision Records</strong></li><li>Ambulance pattern</li><li>Outbreak Cache</li><li>Dividing Data Stores<ul><li>Better access control by user types</li><li>Better availability</li></ul></li><li>Risk Storming<ul><li>Make Matrix<ul><li>Availability</li><li>Elasticity</li><li>Security</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="context">Context<a class="hash-link" href="#context" title="Direct link to heading">â€‹</a></h2><p>I've been in a project which is based on Microsevice Architecture and Event Driven Architecture. (with k8s and Kafka)</p>]]></content:encoded>
