            <description><![CDATA[Hello from Docusaurus]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="hello-from-docusaurus">Hello from Docusaurus<a class="hash-link" href="#hello-from-docusaurus" title="Direct link to heading">â€‹</a></h2><p>This is the first blog post with <a href="https://docusaurus.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Docusaurus</a>. (ver <code>2.2.0</code>)</p><p>It's quite easy to write document, posts and etc with Docusaurus, so I decided to use it also for my own website.</p><p><em>(If you're thinking of writing UMLs with PlantUML in Docusaurus, you should know Docusaurus, as of now, uses PlantUML's public API to render UML images.)</em></p><p>I like how intuitive it is to organize markdown (and other) files to build a website with it.</p><p>Previously I used <a href="https://www.getzola.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">zola</a>, which is not so bad but a bit awkward to customize and build...</p><p>But now I'm in a positive mood to post my reading notes or misc thoughts here.</p>]]></content:encoded>
